WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:59.810 --> 00:02:05.480
Millet Dumplings

3
00:03:11.670 --> 00:03:13.260
Kaido!

4
00:03:16.680 --> 00:03:21.100
This one's gonna end it, Kaido!

5
00:03:51.960 --> 00:03:52.840
Not now!

6
00:03:57.970 --> 00:03:59.720
Straw Hat?!

7
00:03:59.720 --> 00:04:01.350
When did you get hit?!

8
00:04:01.350 --> 00:04:03.220
That's not what happened.

9
00:04:03.220 --> 00:04:06.230
It's a side effect of that
wrecking ball technique!

10
00:04:06.230 --> 00:04:09.560
He won't be able to use haki
for about ten minutes!

11
00:04:09.560 --> 00:04:13.440
Makes sense. All that power comes at a cost.

12
00:04:13.440 --> 00:04:18.030
Still, if all of those punches actually hurt him,

13
00:04:18.030 --> 00:04:20.320
now's our chance to finish the job!

14
00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:28.870
Don't push your luck!

15
00:04:37.090 --> 00:04:40.050
Luffy! You're dead if you don't get moving!

16
00:04:44.220 --> 00:04:47.430
What's that? Already tapped out?

17
00:04:47.430 --> 00:04:50.020
That was quite the tantrum!

18
00:04:50.690 --> 00:04:54.190
But now, it's lights out for you!

19
00:04:54.770 --> 00:04:55.860
Happy Mother's...

20
00:04:56.280 --> 00:04:57.360
Blaze!

21
00:05:01.990 --> 00:05:04.830
Now hand over Straw Hat!

22
00:05:08.540 --> 00:05:09.790
Countershock!

23
00:05:17.340 --> 00:05:19.300
Luffy! Wake up!

24
00:05:30.350 --> 00:05:33.560
Let's keep up the pressure on Kaido, Killer!

25
00:05:33.560 --> 00:05:34.730
Okay!

26
00:06:09.640 --> 00:06:11.850
Killer! Watch out!

27
00:06:29.080 --> 00:06:32.200
The wind that blows heavenward...

28
00:06:32.200 --> 00:06:35.080
destroys all in its wake...

29
00:06:35.080 --> 00:06:37.420
Dragon Twister!

30
00:06:40.550 --> 00:06:41.760
Killer!

31
00:06:50.600 --> 00:06:52.480
You've got to be kidding!

32
00:06:52.480 --> 00:06:55.270
It's like a natural disaster!

33
00:06:57.690 --> 00:07:01.070
Zoro...! Thanks...

34
00:07:01.070 --> 00:07:02.110
Yeah.

35
00:07:15.460 --> 00:07:16.670
Luffy!

36
00:07:29.970 --> 00:07:31.600
Hold it!

37
00:07:31.600 --> 00:07:34.980
You don't get to eat our captain,
you son of a bitch!

38
00:08:20.350 --> 00:08:22.150
I see!

39
00:08:23.820 --> 00:08:29.200
That strange haki is coming from his sword!

40
00:08:45.130 --> 00:08:46.590
Three-Sword Style:

41
00:08:47.380 --> 00:08:50.130
Black Rope Great Dragon Twister!

42
00:09:04.770 --> 00:09:06.230
He sliced through his scales!

43
00:09:13.280 --> 00:09:16.490
That punk! He cut Kaido!

44
00:09:21.210 --> 00:09:23.960
Oh, you got me good!

45
00:09:24.630 --> 00:09:26.300
I see...

46
00:09:26.300 --> 00:09:29.260
Just as I thought, that sword...

47
00:09:31.090 --> 00:09:34.800
belonged to Oden, didn't it?

48
00:09:40.940 --> 00:09:44.190
You dare to challenge
my own Dragon Twister...

49
00:09:44.190 --> 00:09:47.190
I'll put you in your place!

50
00:10:05.040 --> 00:10:06.920
Hey! Luffy!

51
00:10:06.920 --> 00:10:08.920
Oh, Zoro...?

52
00:10:14.680 --> 00:10:16.100
Something big is coming!

53
00:10:23.100 --> 00:10:25.150
Dragon Twister...

54
00:10:25.600 --> 00:10:28.610
Demolition Gust!

55
00:11:06.230 --> 00:11:07.940
What a pain...

56
00:11:22.330 --> 00:11:24.620
First, our supplier dies,

57
00:11:24.620 --> 00:11:30.630
then the banquet that we're
invited to turns into a battlefield.

58
00:11:31.050 --> 00:11:35.590
Cipher Pol Aigis 0
World's Most Powerful Intelligence Agency

59
00:11:37.590 --> 00:11:42.560
Apparently, this battle is to avenge a man
who was killed in Wano twenty years ago.

60
00:11:44.680 --> 00:11:46.100
Yeah...

61
00:11:46.100 --> 00:11:49.770
But when Doflamingo fell from power,

62
00:11:49.770 --> 00:11:53.940
this clash between Kaido
and the Worst Generation became inevitable.

63
00:11:53.940 --> 00:11:56.570
It was fate...

64
00:11:57.110 --> 00:12:00.740
that brought the samurai
and the pirates together.

65
00:12:02.450 --> 00:12:06.580
With the world order
hanging on a knife's edge...

66
00:12:07.620 --> 00:12:13.000
Imagine if both of those
Emperors were to somehow fall...

67
00:12:17.010 --> 00:12:20.590
There's no telling what would
happen to the world.

68
00:12:24.060 --> 00:12:26.270
But we needn't worry about that.

69
00:12:30.310 --> 00:12:34.110
The enemy invaders...

70
00:12:34.940 --> 00:12:40.110
number 5,400.

71
00:12:40.110 --> 00:12:42.570
But 400 have fallen.

72
00:12:46.120 --> 00:12:48.410
On the other hand,

73
00:12:48.410 --> 00:12:53.290
we Beast Pirates...

74
00:12:53.290 --> 00:12:57.170
number 30,000.

75
00:12:57.170 --> 00:12:59.170
But 3,000 of them have already fallen.

76
00:13:00.430 --> 00:13:03.390
The samurai have done well.

77
00:13:06.180 --> 00:13:10.940
The difference in numbers is so vast
that a direct attack would never reach the leader.

78
00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:16.150
Their infiltration plan
has worked out brilliantly.

79
00:13:16.980 --> 00:13:22.450
But in this battle, simply taking
the leader's head won't cut it.

80
00:13:24.200 --> 00:13:38.380
(27000)

81
00:13:25.200 --> 00:13:29.370
This is an all-out war.
There's no refuge on the island.

82
00:13:29.960 --> 00:13:34.290
If Kaido's top officers are left unchecked...

83
00:13:34.290 --> 00:13:37.800
each will easily eliminate
100 soldiers at a time.

84
00:13:38.880 --> 00:13:43.340
If this new generation
can't stop the top officers...

85
00:13:44.390 --> 00:13:49.060
...this game of go will end
with all black pieces on the board.

86
00:13:52.440 --> 00:13:55.440
The outcome of this battle
has already been decided.

87
00:13:58.980 --> 00:14:02.110
Crush one another as much as you want...

88
00:14:02.910 --> 00:14:05.030
my dear pirates.

89
00:14:20.670 --> 00:14:23.680
Why does he look like that?

90
00:14:23.680 --> 00:14:25.890
Is that his hybrid form?

91
00:14:26.390 --> 00:14:28.810
Hey, Linlin!

92
00:14:28.810 --> 00:14:30.720
Isn't this fun?

93
00:14:35.020 --> 00:14:38.900
You took the words right out of my mouth!

94
00:14:43.950 --> 00:14:46.820
Kaido!

95
00:14:49.120 --> 00:14:51.160
Listen up, fellas!

